    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels; the Test conditions factor achieves level 1 against a required level of 2, but this shortfall is accepted because the COU is explicitly bounded to the single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration and no generalization beyond this condition is asserted. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design. Note: aleatory uncertainty contributions from inter-specimen material variability and cross-laboratory setup differences are discussed qualitatively in the validation report; formal UQ artifacts have been linked for stiffness and yield force results, but the force-at-40-mm ValidationResult does not carry a linked uncertainty quantification node, representing a gap to be addressed in subsequent credibility updates.",
